\subsubsection{Economic parameters}
Farm harvest price for the crops under consideration were obtained from district-level inventory data compiled by ICRISAT. Diesel price, fertiliser price were obtained from the same source. These prices were adjusted for inflation using the consumer price index with 2010 as a reference year. The cost of tubewell installation and purchase of a new pump were obtained from field reports. The average lifespan of a tubewell and groundwater pump were obtained from various literature estimates for the Indo-Gangetic Plain. 

\subsection{Initial conditions}
We estimated the proportion of farms receiving canal water using village-level census data included in a recent geospatial socio-economic dataset for India \citep{meiyappan_dynamics_2017}, which includes the gross area irrigated from various sources including canals and private tubewells. We combined this information with district-level data from the Minor Irrigation Census detailing the number of tubewells in operation to obtain an estimate of the number of tubewells present in each village. We mapped this data to a spatial grid using... interpolation.

India's Minor Irrigation Censuses details on a district-wise basis the number of tubwells commissioned in each year since 1982-83, as well as the total number comissioned prior to 1982-83, the number of tubewells according to power source (e.g. electric, diesel), and the number of tubewells in use according to land holding size. Additionally, the censuses detail the area by groundwater and surfacewater schemes during the three main growing seasons (kharif, rabi, perennial). The agricultural census data compiled by ICRISAT show the number of farms according to land holding size.

